assessment_comment: Adjacent landowner Lorenzo indicated that in 30 years of owning the land all the way to the Fraser and well upstream of the crossing he has never seen salmon come to spawn. He also indicated that the stream dries up completely each year.

Channell has filled in nicely since last year. Numerous sockeye holding upstream and downstream of the Crossing. Multiple large dead Spond out sockeye present. Live cuttings appear to be growing however year two and three will be better indicators of success for revegetation.
